{"parse":{"title":"Diversity in open source software","pageid":54281870,"revid":834403271,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Open-source_software_movement\" title=\"Open-source software movement\">open-source software movement</a> is commonly cited to have a diversity problem that reflects that <a href=\"/wiki/Gender_disparity_in_computing\" title=\"Gender disparity in computing\">gender disparity in computing</a> but in general is assumed to be even more severe or different in some ways.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Gender_diversity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gender diversity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Racial_and_ethnic_diversity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Racial and ethnic diversity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Sexual_minority_diversity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sexual minority diversity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gender_diversity\">Gender diversity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diversity_in_open_source_software&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Gender diversity\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The gender ratio in open source is even greater than the field wide gender disparity in computing. This has been found by a number of surveys:\n</p>\n<ul><li>A 2002 survey of 2,784 open source software developers found that 1.1% of them were women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>A 2013 survey of 2,183 open source contributors found that 81.4% were men and 10.4% were women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> This survey included both software contributors and non-software contributors and women were much more likely to be non-software contributors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>A 2017 survey of 5,500 contributors to projects on <a href=\"/wiki/GitHub\" title=\"GitHub\">GitHub</a> found that 95% of contributors were men and 3% were women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Klint2016Wired_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Klint2016Wired-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>In 2015 <a href=\"/wiki/RedHat\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RedHat\">RedHat</a> started the Women in Open Source Awards.\nThe winners are:<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li>2017 Community Award winner <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Avni_Khatri&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Avni Khatri (page does not exist)\">Avni Khatri</a></li>\n<li>2017 Academic Award winner <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jigyasa_Grover&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jigyasa Grover (page does not exist)\">Jigyasa Grover</a></li>\n<li>2016 Community Award winner <a href=\"/wiki/Jessica_McKellar\" title=\"Jessica McKellar\">Jessica McKellar</a></li>\n<li>2016 Academic Award winner <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Preeti_Murthy&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Preeti Murthy (page does not exist)\">Preeti Murthy</a></li>\n<li>2015 Community Award winner <a href=\"/wiki/Sarah_Sharp\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sarah Sharp\">Sarah Sharp</a></li>\n<li>2015 Academic Award winner <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Kesha_Shah&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Kesha Shah (page does not exist)\">Kesha Shah</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Racial_and_ethnic_diversity\">Racial and ethnic diversity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diversity_in_open_source_software&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Racial and ethnic diversity\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Black_people\" title=\"Black people\">Black people</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Latino\" title=\"Latino\">Latinos</a> are considered to be underrepresented.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sexual_minority_diversity\">Sexual minority diversity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diversity_in_open_source_software&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Sexual minority diversity\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A higher percentage of open source contributors are members of a <a href=\"/wiki/Sexual_minority\" title=\"Sexual minority\">sexual minority</a>. A 2017 survey of GitHub contributors found that 7% were <a href=\"/wiki/LGBT\" title=\"LGBT\">LGBT</a> compared to 4% of the general population.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Klint2016Wired_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Klint2016Wired-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Diversity_in_open_source_software&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://flossproject.merit.unu.edu/report/Final4.htm\">http://flossproject.merit.unu.edu/report/Final4.htm</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"FLOSS 2013: A Survey Dataset about Free Software Contributors: Challenges for Curating, Sharing, and Combining\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.win.tue.nl/~aserebre/msr14gregorio.pdf\">https://www.win.tue.nl/~aserebre/msr14gregorio.pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Women in Free/Libre/Open Source Software: The situation in the 2010s\".</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Klint2016Wired-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Klint2016Wired_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Klint2016Wired_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Klint, Finley (2 June 2017). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.wired.com/2017/06/diversity-open-source-even-worse-tech-overall/\">\"Diversity in Open Source Is Even Worse Than in Tech Overall\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Wired_(magazine)\" title=\"Wired (magazine)\">Wired</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Wired&amp;rft.atitle=Diversity+in+Open+Source+Is+Even+Worse+Than+in+Tech+Overall&amp;rft.date=2017-06-02&amp;rft.aulast=Klint&amp;rft.aufirst=Finley&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2F2017%2F06%2Fdiversity-open-source-even-worse-tech-overall%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADiversity+in+open+source+software\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.redhat.com/en/about/women-in-open-source#2015finalists\">\"Women in Open Source Awards\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">Feb 3,</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Women+in+Open+Source+Awards&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.redhat.com%2Fen%2Fabout%2Fwomen-in-open-source%232015finalists&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADiversity+in+open+source+software\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Why Isn't Open Source A Gateway For Coders Of Color?\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.npr.org/sections/codeswitch/2013/12/05/248791579/why-isnt-open-source-a-gateway-for-coders-of-color\">https://www.npr.org/sections/codeswitch/2013/12/05/248791579/why-isnt-open-source-a-gateway-for-coders-of-color</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1275\nCached time: 20180909055535\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.060 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.074 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 138/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 2610/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 3/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstri